reviews.title: Hospitable, well cared for, delicious food
reviews.text:
We had dinner here with a large group (+30). The reservation had to be adjusted several times. This was very easy.
The various dishes were all excellent, the service great. Everyone was very satisfied. Thank you

reviews.title: Very bad
reviews.text:
Place an order by telephone and receive a call back an hour later with the message that the shawarma has run out.....
How!!!! 
Very very bad and disappointing!

reviews.title: Don`t do it (take- away)
reviews.text: We used the take- away service once and never again. The pasta arrabiata was not arrabiata, no spices, and it had anchovis in it (I never saw a recipe to get a fishy taste in pasta arrabiata), the italian salad contained a few large leaves, too little dressing and did not taste like an italian salad at all. The lasagne was ok, not really good. And information would help: we did not know that with every meal there is a small salad included anyway, so we had way too much salad. Aand also here: too little dressing.

reviews.title: Limited choice of drinks.
reviews.text: New management? Meals fresh and tasty, all female serving staff seemed oddly shy and reticent. Decor simple and clean. Decent menu choice. Staff try to be friendly but not sure how.  I’d eat there again but there’s an old feel to the place! Nice Italian red wine.

reviews.title: No exciting meals or service
reviews.text:
With really young waiters, perhaps you can't expect the best service. On the other hand, why not? They don't get paid for just sitting around. Anyway, they weren't very quick or eager to ask for our order, nor to actually bring the cutlery after we had received our food.

The food itself was okay. My dish (cannoli) was pretty salty even though the tomatopaste made it kind of sour as well. The other people in my party weren't very excited about their dishes. Like I said, it was okay but with many more restaurants in the area I would not choose to go here again.

reviews.title: Dispointed
reviews.text:
Well, my husband ordered mix grill. What he got was shaorma tested like rubber and  few pieces of meet that was not that tasty.. i asked Flafel. I got five super small Flafel with fries (which i was 100% sure that the cooking was used alooot of times because it didnt smell good) and some vigetables aside for €12.50 !!!! Flafel are usually cheap man !! 
Anyways  i expected way more for a mediterranean resturant :-(

reviews.text:
In Oase there was a famous German comedian, Bernard Hoeker. He also was very content with the food. 😄  
Excellent and friendly staff.

reviews.title: Very nice experience
reviews.text: if this is the restaurant own by Emad Wahba, then yes, it was a marvelous experience. We ordered grilled meat (kofta, meat skewers and shawarma) and the portion as well as the quality of the food were fantastic. Very friendly staff and very cozy atmosphere. I loved it!

reviews.title: If there is no alternative......
reviews.text:
Simple restaurant in the central place of Harlingen. Menu offers mainly Pizzas, Pasta and some meat dishes.
Pizza was ok. Salad with chicken we didn't like (not very tasty).
Prices are upper end with around 12 € for a Pizza. 
3.50€ for some small pieces of bread and some butter is ridiculous.
Service is friendly.

reviews.title: Conveniant place for a easy meal.
reviews.text: We visited the Oase during The Tall Ship Races 2014 event. We wanted to have a dinner together with our host at the end of the afternoon / beginning of the evening because we wanted to be home in time for the football game between the Netherlands and Costa Rica. We could not make a reservation. We found a good table although the place was very crowded with people taking a rest after visiting the event. The menu mainly consists of Mediterranean food. We had a good tasty meal and there was a lot. So the restaurant delivered everything we looked for and we managed to get back home in time to watch the Netherlands beat Costa Rica in a very exciting game

reviews.title: Extremely bad attitude. RUDE
reviews.text: My husband and I had dinner last night at Oase and will never return. The food is adequate but the attitude of staff, both the waitress and manager, were extraordinary. Perhaps the language barrier accounted for the first problem. I said I would like sparkling mineral water and then my husband said he would like a large bottle. We were surprised to be brought two glasses (one small, one large) rather than the bottle. We then tried it and found it to be totally flat.  We told the waitress this and asked her to please bring a bottle Mathis she did, but no additional glasses.  I drank part of my water and poured the rest into the large glass so that we had one empty one into which to pour the new water.  Later in the meal I handed the waitress the full glass to take away.  When presented with our bill, we were charged four euros for the flat water!  I pointed out that it had been unsatisfactory and she said we had drunk one glass and the absolute best they could do was charge us for one instead of two.  We had only drunk their poor water to free up a glass.  She then involved the manager who supported her position. I cannot recommend this restaurant!

reviews.title: Super , Relaxt , and a great team
reviews.text: Every week i buy a pizza by Oase....Why ?!!!  Because they are Wunderfull, nice personel, and delicious food.   Sabah.....you are the best cook in the world.

reviews.title: Great place gonna come here again!
reviews.text: Very good food en friendly staff. I recommend the spare ribs Hot. Also Pizza 63 Oase speciale. Kitchenstaff are magician with food

reviews.title: Nice pizzas here.
reviews.text: Reasonably priced menu with pizza and pastas amongst other things. Decent service, too. I'd go back if I'm ever in Harlingen again.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

Berlin is nothing if not resilient, having outlasted many turbulent periods in its history. Those scars still show today in the stark distinction felt between the east and west sides of the city even though it’s been decades since the Berlin Wall came down. And for a European capital city, it’s not conventionally beautiful like Paris or London. Instead, Berlin embraces its eccentric hodgepodge of grit and glamour.
This perfect two-day Amsterdam itinerary includes pretty neighborhoods, top attractions, and canal exploration based on Tripadvisor reviews and ratings.

articleContent.title: How to walk the Las Vegas Strip at night

seoInfo.metaDescription: Whenever I’m in Las Vegas my absolute favorite pastime is walking the Strip at night. That’s when the city’s massive casino resorts are at their most mesmerizing, wowing even a repeat visitor like me with synchronized fountains and incredible replicas of world-famous landmarks made all the more dazzling by a gazillion neon and LED lights. While this could border on Disneyesque, the Strip’s edgy, anything-goes vibe makes it the ideal spot to get swept up in the city’s notorious sensory overload—which, as a New Yorker, I can relate to.
